"name":"Resolve_Links","description":""}]}},{"id":"2cad80ee361b35f7","name":"Name","qualified_name":"Den.Name","kind":"ada_function","location":{"file":"src/den.ads","line":207,"column":13},"code":"function Name (This : Path) return Part","documentation":{"description":"Just the last component in the path; the name of a root is itself.","parameters":[{"name":"This","description":""}]}},{"id":"476c3e07621f0e35","name":"Normal","qualified_name":"Den.Normal","kind":"ada_function","location":{"file":"src/den.ads","line":114,"column":13},"code":"function Normal (This : Path) return Normal_Path","documentation":{"description":"Remove \".\", \"..\" from path, but without first making it absolute, so it\nmay raise even for valid relative paths. Use Normal (Absolute (This)) in\nsuch cases. Too many \"..\" (going \"up\" of root) will also raise.","parameters":[{"name":"This","description":""}]}},{"id":"9299579730ca92d7","name":"Parent","qualified_name":"Den.Parent","kind":"ada_function","location":{"file":"src/den.ads","line":221,"column":13},"code":"function Parent (This : Path) return Path","documentation":{"description":"Will not try to obtain absolute paths, nor canonalize nor do any\nother processing. See Canonical_Parent for that.","parameters":[{"name":"This","description":""}]}},{"id":"bb235f2a158cc7e0","name":"Parts","qualified_name":"Den.Parts","kind":"ada_function","location":{"file":"src/den.ads","line":106,"column":13},"code":"function Parts (This : Path) return Path_Parts"},{"id":"2adfabdb2a2a600c","name":"Resolve","qualified_name":"Den.Resolve","kind":"ada_function","location":{"file":"src/den.ads","line":174,"column":13},"code":"function Resolve (This : Path) return Path","documentation":{"description":"Identity for non-links, else change This for its target without further\nprocessing. Note that the result might be a new soft link. Intermediate\nsoftlinks are not resolved either. Use with care, prefer Canonical.\nNote also that Scrub will be performed on Target (This), so use Target\nfor the raw contents of a softlink. May raise if the result is not a\nwell-formed Path even after scrubbing.","parameters":[{"name":"This","description":""}]}},{"id":"2e18df96d81eff69","name":"Root","qualified_name":"Den.Root","kind":"ada_function","location":{"file":"src/den.ads","line":172,"column":13},"code":"function Root (This : Absolute_Path) return Root_Path"},{"id":"37b143c6a4addc9d","name":"Safe_Parent","qualified_name":"Den.Safe_Parent","kind":"ada_function","location":{"file":"src/den.ads","line":226,"column":13},"code":"function Safe_Parent (This : Path) return Path","documentation":{"description":"Always get a parent, even for simple names. This introduces implicit\ndependency on the current directory.","parameters":[{"name":"This","description":""}]}},{"id":"9aa47fe95f2e8365","name":"Scrub","qualified_name":"Den.Scrub","kind":"ada_function","location":{"file":"src/den.ads","line":73,"column":13},"code":"function Scrub (This : String) return Path","documentation":{"description":"Fix trailing '/' and duplicated \"//\". May raise Bad_Path if no good path\nremains after scrubbing. Will respect initial '\\\\' on Windows.\n\nDOES NOT fix reversed slashes. This means that using non-platform\nseparators will be interpreted as any other character.","parameters":[{"name":"This","description":""}]}},{"id":"8a3c15488f25253b","name":"Simple_Name","qualified_name":"Den.Simple_Name","kind":"ada_function","location":{"file":"src/den.ads","line":211,"column":13},"code":"function Simple_Name (This : Path) return Part","documentation":{"description":"For Ada.Directories compatibility","parameters":[{"name":"This","description":""}]}},{"id":"c34f957baa854003","name":"String_Is_Root","qualified_name":"Den.String_Is_Root","kind":"ada_function","location":{"file":"src/den.ads","line":166,"column":13},"code":"function String_Is_Root (This : String) return Boolean","documentation":{"description":"Used to break recursion among predicates","parameters":[{"name":"This","description":""}]}},{"id":"cdb02c5d1befedc3","name":"Target","qualified_name":"Den.Target","kind":"ada_function","location":{"file":"src/den.ads","line":242,"column":13},"code":"function Target (This : Path) return String","documentation":{"description":"The target of a softlink, even if broken, or the original path given.\nThis returns the information proper stored in the softlink, not the\noriginal path with the target replacing the softlink, use Resolve for\nthat. The returned result is not normalized or resolved, use Full_Path\nfor that. Note that the result may be not a proper path, e.g. something\nlike \"mal//formed\". Use Scrub to clean such things.","parameters":[{"name":"This","description":""}]}},{"id":"6d16314fc150f1f7","name":"Target_Exists","qualified_name":"Den.Target_Exists","kind":"ada_function","location":{"file":"src/den.ads","line":161,"column":13},"code":"function Target_Exists (This : Path) return Boolean"},{"id":"bf7963b607f93611","name":"Target_Kind","qualified_name":"Den.Target_Kind","kind":"ada_function","location":{"file":"src/den.ads","line":148,"column":13},"code":"function Target_Kind (This : Path) return Kinds","documentation":{"description":"May still return softlink if the softlink is unresolvable","parameters":[{"name":"This","description":""}]}},{"id":"5ae875dedee29720","name":"Target_Length","qualified_name":"Den.Target_Length","kind":"ada_function","location":{"file":"src/den.ads","line":237,"column":13},"code":"function Target_Length (This : Path) return Natural","documentation":{"description":"The length of a softlink target name. Not generally useful to clients\nbut who knows...","parameters":[{"name":"This","description":""}]}},{"id":"29070befa4fe756d","name":"To_Path","qualified_name":"Den.To_Path","kind":"ada_function","location":{"file":"src/den.ads","line":87,"column":13},"code":"function To_Path (This : Path_Parts) return String"}],"packages":[{"id":"0655b3582be1110f","name":"Operators","qualified_name":"Den.Operators","kind":"ada_package","location":{"file":"src/den.ads","line":255,"column":12},"code":"package Operators"}]}